<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/868b: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-17T14:00:00-04:00">August 17, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>135. Please inform me immediately whether you would be able to
                                    deliver a confidential message to Mussolini himself from this
                                    Government. Is the Chief of Government in Rome, or, if not, how
                                    soon could such a message be delivered to him by you?</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>